headline: Midterm Fight Over Trump Bill, Tariffs Starts Early at Iowa Fair
summary: In it, Nunn, one of the nation’s most vulnerable incumbents, talks to constituent Sarah Curry about how the expanded child tax credit will help with the cost of one child’s speech therapy.  Nunn is also planning to use the state fair as the backdrop for more videos selling the bill’s provisions temporarily cutting taxes on tips and overtime.  Economic issues — namely, Trump’s tax package and his tariff war with countries that buy much of Iowa’s agricultural products — will be front and center in Nunn’s race, and he’s eager to get a jumpstart defining the issues.
